'''Amri culture''' is attributed to Amri archaeological sites in [[Sindh]] and [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]] provinces of [[Pakistan]]. It flourished in the 4th and 3rd millennia BC. The [[typesite]] is [[Amri, Sindh]].

At least 160 settlements attributed to the Amri Culture have been discovered, mainly in [[Balochistan (Pakistan)|Balochistan]], but also in lower [[Sindh]]. They are often distributed along the terraces of old and active river courses and consist of sites of different size and shape, which are sometimes stratified below settlements of later periods. Among these, that of the [[Tharro Hills]], near the town of [[Gujo]], is one of the most famous of lower Sindh.

